- Goes to the Commits tab where there are 3 commits.\
- Reads the commit messages.\
- Sees that the author first created the init, then generated chabgelogs, the third message the reviewer doesn\'92t understand very well but just wants to see it in the code then.\
- Goes to the Changes tab.\
- When the PR is huge, then the reviewer looks commit by commit to see how the code changes through time. But at the simpler reviews like this one, they just go see the diff.\
- The reviewer firstly hovers with the mouse through the list of affected files.\
- Sees that the author added a folder with a script that does something very generic - initialises the testing. So let\'92s see what that means.\
- Then there is a file with projects that lists all their static websites, the related gitlab repo and a file path of the package.json file in there. The author probably needs that to generate the tests based on that directory.\
